through ingrained habits of experienced designers. An  examination of claims, their uses in design, and the possibilities for  explicit use in future collaborative design endeavors seeks to inspire their  further development use in HCI design. </p> <p class=\"last\"> Table of Contents: What are Claims? / Knowing and Sharing / Evolution of Claims / Using Claims / Looking Forward </p> </div><!-- /abstract content --><!-- fulltext content --><!-- /fulltext content -->\n\n        <div class=\"article_link\">\n        <table align=\"center\" cellspacing=\"10\">\n        <tr>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n    \n    \n    \n    \n        \n            <td align=\"center\" nowrap=\"nowrap\">\n                <a href=\"/doi/pdf/10.2200/S00423ED1V01Y201205HCI015\" class=\"header4\" target=\"_blank\">\n                    PDF\n                    <span class=\"fileSize\">\n                        \n                        (3897 KB)\n                    </span>\n                </a>\n            </td>\n            \n    \n            \n            <td align=\"center\" nowrap=\"nowrap\">\n                <a href=\"/doi/pdfplus/10.2200/S00423ED1V01Y201205HCI015\" class=\"header4\" target=\"_blank\">\n                    PDF Plus\n                    <span class=\"fileSize\">\n                        \n                        (3344 KB)\n                    </span>\n                </a>\n            </td>\n            \n       \n        \n        \n\n    \n    \n    \n\n\n</tr>\n        </table>\n        </div>\n\n        \n        \n        <div class=\"citedBySection\" id=\"citart1\"><a name=\"citedBySection\"></a><h2>Cited by</h2><div class=\"citedByEntry\"><span class=\"name noWrap\">Joon Suk<span class=\"NLM_x\"> </span>Lee</span><span class=\"NLM_x\"><x>, </x></span><span class=\"name noWrap\">Margaret<span class=\"NLM_x\"> </span>Dickey-Kurdziolek</span><span class=\"NLM_x\"><x>, </x></span><span class=\"name noWrap\">Stacy<span class=\"NLM_x\"> </span>Branham</span><span class=\"wbr\"